[normal]3a 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]How reliable is the Government’s forecast for growth in demand for the strategic road network?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]In 
[normal]the light of the recently-published National Traffic Survey's figures on traffic for 2012, which
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]show
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]an overall decline
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]compared with those of 10 years
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]earlier, it is tempting to dismiss it out
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]of
[normal] hand as based
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]on a mixture of wishful thinking
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]and
[normal] simple guesswork. Worryingly, it assumes
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]that
[normal] current dips in numbers
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]result solely from present austerity, and so will rise once "growth"
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]returns
[normal]. We doubt this,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]given the increasing environmental awareness of the population as a whole,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]and
[normal] 
[normal]also the inherent unevenness
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]of such signs of growth already claimed - the numbers of young
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]people
[normal] acquiring cars, for instance, are in
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]continuing decline, for whatever reason(s) this may be -
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]and
[normal] it will always be difficult usefully to generalise
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]about individual decisions of any sort.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The only consistently-upward trend in any mode of transport, which has lasted for at least the last
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]10 years,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]without exception, is that in passenger rail journeys, recession or no recession. Highways
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]policy
[normal] in its
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]wider sense must always take this into account.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
