[normal]than the UK since 1990, blithely ignoring the fact that
[normal]              
[normal]France occupies a much larger
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]area
[normal] in 
[normal]relation
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]to its population than does the UK. It then mentions the fact that, in the same
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]period
[normal], 6 new
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]TGV rail
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]lines have been constructed, involving a similarly impressive total length,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]but
[normal], equally blithely, ignores
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]the obvious reaction - where 
[normal]are
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]their UK counterparts? If there had
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]been
[normal] an equal enthusiasm, during
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]the same 20+ years, for improving our rail network with similar
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]new
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]high-speed lines, rather than just
[normal]&#xa0;
